Actually, my first thought was the fight between Superman and the 3 Super-villians (General Zod and his 2 cohorts) in Superman II.  But the scene was very Dragonaballesqué.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I must say I seriously pity all of you people who are running over the plot with fine tooth comb and hating these movies, you're setting yourself up for disappointment.  The Matrix is SO MUCH more enjoyable if you don't force yourself to try and understand every single little friggin tiny and insignificant concept.  I don't understand 100% of it, but I get enough so that I understand why things are happening that are happening and why the outcome of what's happening is important, and I never got lost.  And since I didn't waste my energy tring to firgure out shit like, &quot;why are Agent Smith's Sunglasses crooked, is that glitch in the program, DEAR GOD SOMEBODY TELL ME THIS MOVIE SUX!!1?&quot; I was able to just enjoy a damn well done movie, ALL 3 PARTS KICKED ASS!  I do admit, Reloaded was my least favorite out of the 3, but it still delivered and entertained me.  It's, dare I say, arrogant, to expect these movies to fulfill your need to pick apart a plot to bare bones and have everything answered for you.  Just relax and enjoy, and you'll be a happier person. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tryon Briarwood</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.xevnull.com">NULL</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
