<br>
Tyrene,<br>
The Oracle was the mother of the matrix, and a program created to understand humans.  The idea was that every time you had a choice to make, that was the oracle working behind the scenes.  There was no real choice... you have already made it... your &quot;purpose&quot; was to understand WHY you made it.<br>
<br>
There is no spoon.<br>
<br>
As Smith grew in power (by taking over every aspect of the matrix he could) he was changing it.  What shocked me so much was how quick the oracle recovered, but knowing that the real actress died helps that to make a little more sense.  The Oracle knew she was going to fall to Smith and she knew she couldn't stop him.  She knew that Smith would take over the entire world (the matrix world) and that Neo was the only force that could stop Smith.  She also SEEMED to know that the only way to end the war between the machines and the humans was to make them settle the conclict in reality.  I think this was something she had in mind when she created the (edit from 5th) 6th matrix, Neo, AND Smith (ballencing the equasion).  If you watch, you see her guide Neo through the process of becoming aware as a human, then conecting with machines.  Once he understood their ability to &quot;feel&quot; he knew how to end the war betwen human and machine.<br>
As for the Oracle, I think her physical connection to the matrix was an after-thought, that's why it was a weaker part of the story.  She changed because the matrix had changed so much.  I think Merovigian knew this and could tell the matrix was changing as Smith took over every part of it.  He knew that as the matrix changed, the oracle would to.<br>
Like I said, this was one of the weaker storylines, but it fits in.  They didn't need it, but it looks like they only used it becasue they had to.<br>
<br>
I haven't seen the game either.  I don't plan on it, actually.  It makes sense to me as is. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tibult>tibult</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~nnettles/Nick1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/9/03 9:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dramid>Dramid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#330000>(11/9/03 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1118.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Matrix Revolutions...</span><hr size=1> As for &quot;not getting the movie&quot; . I very much get what they were trying to say I just think the way they said is stupid. <p>Cleramid<br>
